Metal sheet.wikitext:
{{topicon Fandom|Tattered_metal_sheet}}
{{interlangbox}}
{{#invoke:Scraps/AutoInfobox|infobox
| scrap = MetalSheet
}}
The '''Metal sheet''' (or "Tattered metal sheet") is a heavy, low-value [[Scrap]] that's commonly found on low-tier moons. Due to its weight and value, it can be argued that it's the worst item in the entire game.

[[File:Metal_sheet_variants.webp|thumb|right|Both variants of Metal sheets]]
[[File:Back of Metal sheet.png|thumb|An employee holding a Metal sheet from a 3rd person perspective, to show the steel bolt textures found on the back.]]

== Item Variants ==
There are 2 possible appearances of the Metal sheet:

* A sheet with more jagged edges, horizontal lines with a seam down the middle, 4 holes torn through it, and 7 steel bolts attached to the back (Commonly referred to by players as the "4-hole" sheet)
* A sheet with more straight edges, vertical lines, 2 holes torn through it, and 8 steel bolts attached to the back (Commonly referred to by players as the "2-hole" sheet)

The default appearance is the 4-hole sheet, which will be chosen upon reloading a save file containing the item due to the game not saving item variants.

== Trivia ==

* As briefly mentioned above, both variants of Metal sheet have some steel bolts attached to the back, which you might not ever notice in-game due to them being located on the underside of the sheet while it's on the floor. It is fairly easy to see while looking at somebody else holding the item though.

