Painting.wikitext:
{{topicon Fandom}}
{{interlangbox}}
{{#invoke:Scraps/AutoInfobox|infobox
| scrap = FancyPainting
}}

The '''Painting''' is a high-value [[Scrap]] that can be found on some paid moons, that can spawn in 2 different variants. Although it appears that you hold it in one hand, it makes your [[hands full]].

[[File:Painting_variants.webp|thumb|right|Both variants of Paintings]]

== Item Variants ==
There are 2 possible appearances of the Painting:

* A bright, cloudy sky with a few trees slightly visible at the bottom.
* A large lake with trees seen on the other side, as well as a distant red building & cloudy sky above.

The default appearance is the one primarily depicting a cloudy sky, which will be chosen upon reloading a save file containing the item due to the game not remembering item variants.

== Trivia ==

The two painting variations are small cut-outs taken from different areas of the same larger painting, [[w:Wivenhoe_Park_(painting)|Wivenhoe Park]], by John Constable. This painting is also used in the "fake window" room of [[Mansion|Mansions]] as well as the cow found on a variant of [[Mug]].

