Toy cube.wikitext:
{{topicon Fandom}}
{{interlangbox}}
{{#invoke:Scraps/AutoInfobox|infobox
| scrap = ToyCube
}}
The '''Toy Cube''' stands out as a prevalent one-handed item within the game's item-pool. Notably lightweight, the Toy Cube carries a negligible weight of 0lb, contributing to its ease of use and portability. Visually, it resembles an unsolvable Rubik's Cube.

With respect to its economic value, the Toy Cube possesses a variable scrap value, ranging between 24 and 44 scrap.

An interesting characteristic of the Toy Cube is its exclusion from the pool of items available for [[Experimentation]], despite its status as one of the more common one-handed items.

== Spawn chances ==

{{#invoke:Scraps/AutoTables|spawnChancesOnAllMoonsTables|ToyCube}}

== Trivia ==
[[File:ToyCubeTexture.apparent.webp|thumb|right|The net of the cube as it appears in-game]]
[[File:ToyCubeTexture.webp|thumb|right|The original texture of the cube]]

The Toy cube's texture is not applied to its model correctly.
There's some coloration on what should be a black inner face, but more importantly, the faces have been transposed and rotated in a way that makes the cube unsolvable.
(Take the white&ndash;white edge for example.) Were it laid out as in the texture file, the cube would have been solvable.

